casebody.data:
Daniel IMPERATO, petitioner,
v.
SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION. No. 17-6190. Supreme Court of the United States Nov. 27, 2017.

Motion of petitioner for leave to proceed in forma pauperis denied. Petitioner allowed until December 18, 2017, within *493which to pay the docketing fee required by Rule 38(a) and to submit a petition in compliance with Rule 33.1 of the Rules of this Court.
